- By Geography: North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, Middle East and Africa.

The global diagnostic imaging equipment market is segmented on the basis of product type, application, end user, and geography. In terms of product type, the market is categorized into X-ray systems, MRI systems, ultrasound systems, CT scanners, nuclear imaging systems, mammography systems, and others. Each type of equipment serves a specific purpose in the diagnosis and treatment of various medical conditions. When it comes to applications, diagnostic imaging equipment finds its usage in oncology, cardiology, neurology, orthopedics, gastroenterology, gynecology, and other fields of medicine. Different end users such as hospitals, diagnostic imaging centers, ambulatory surgical centers, and others utilize these imaging systems for accurate diagnosis and patient care. Geographically, the market is divided into five major regions: North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa.

